From 64d557999055da1faa080b97864b7fbb5e225953 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Maksim Ivanov <emaxx@google.com>
Date: Tue, 27 Jan 2026 11:52:58 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] [testing][sandbox] Singleton external strings cage
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Make the cage a process-wide singleton instead of per-isolate-group, to
properly support the case when multiple isolate groups are used.

Also make the cage created and registered at the crash filter earlier,
to reduce the window during which harmless crashes are misclassified.

Bug: 329781444, 479084351
Change-Id: I4ddaa0b95c1741b6b4dbcabd591fc0e664b853b6
Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7516748
Reviewed-by: Omer Katz <omerkatz@chromium.org>
Reviewed-by: Samuel Groß <saelo@chromium.org>
Commit-Queue: Michael Lippautz <mlippautz@chromium.org>
Reviewed-by: Michael Lippautz <mlippautz@chromium.org>
Auto-Submit: Maksim Ivanov <emaxx@chromium.org>
Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/main@{#104929}
